President Trump and President Abbas of the Palestinian Authority met to discuss the possibility of achieving peace in the Middle East. President Trump expressed optimism and said that his team, along with the Israeli government and other nations, are working towards a peace deal. President Abbas thanked President Trump for his efforts and expressed confidence in reaching a real peace agreement. President Trump acknowledged the challenges in achieving peace in the Middle East but emphasized that he is determined to make progress. The leaders also extended their congratulations to the Jewish and Muslim communities on their respective holidays. President Trump did not reveal his decision on the Iran Deal and said that he will announce it later.